<br>
Either one can be solo pulled to the room before it.  On the way there, you have to whack all the thought horrors, and bugs too if you're kos to them.<br>
<br>
The easiest way is with a charmed Ancient Rockhopper if he happens to be up.  He's a tough mother that hits hard and has tons of HP, and he is high enough level that the bugs won't assist thought horrors.  Just solo pull them to the next room (doable at 60, but they're immune to harmony!) and have the pet kill them.  Quick and easy, unless there's an untimely charm break, in which case you get to run around the room a bit and hope you can get the charm off while getting hit once or twice.<br>
<br>
You can do it with some in-door kiting in the next room after the solo-pull, but you'll want scoriae for the speed.  The hive mistress is easily snarable, but the main though horror is a tough one to snare, and will also require some fire debuffing if I remember right.  You might want to pull the thought horror outside the caves with a timely invis to pull him past whatever is up.<br>
<br>
You can do it with a dire charmed mature rockhopper.  The only problem with them is that the bugs assist the thought horrors, so you have a bunch more you have to clear, and you lose faction with the bugs.  They're also not nearly as hoss as the ancient rockhopper, so you have to keep an eye on them, and regen them, etc. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=126501">Abru</a>, Elder Hierophant on The Nameless,  <a href="http://www.legacyofsteel.net/index.shtml" target=_top>Legacy of Steel</a>, <a href="mailto:AbruEQ@hotmail.com">AbruEQ@hotmail.com</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utils.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tils</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.loopi.co.uk/bounce.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/2/02 8:18:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27468.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.loopi.co.uk/tils2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Challenge (well maybe)</span><hr size=1> nice strat!   worked well ..i had  few charm breaks on it and it hits pretty hard so you gotta watch that. Otherwise thats one hella pet hehe<br>
